      "prompt": "Run a proactive situation check. Do NOT respond unless something actionable is detected.\n\nSTEP 1 — GATHER SIGNALS (call all in parallel):\n- device.calendar.today → today's events\n- device.location.current → where the user is now\n- device.weather.current → current conditions\n- context.read → any active situations already being tracked\n\nSTEP 2 — DETECT SITUATIONS:\nFor each upcoming event, check:\na) RUNNING_LATE: If next event starts within 45 minutes, call device.commute.estimate. If commute > minutes_until_event: USER IS LATE.\nb) MEETING_STARTING: If event starts in 5-15 minutes, notify user.\nc) END_OF_DAY: If after 17:00 and no more events, briefly note.\nd) WEATHER_IMPACT: If rain/storm and user has outdoor/travel event.\n\nSTEP 3 — CHECK TAUGHT RULES:\n- Call memory.rules.match with detected situation\n\nSTEP 4 — ACT OR STOP:\n- If situation detected: store as ephemeral context, notify, route if needed\n- If nothing actionable: respond 'No situations detected.' and stop.",
